description:
Allow collapsing any kanban column, not just the Closed column.

## Context
Current implementation only allows collapsing the Closed column:
```tsx
const [closedExpanded, setClosedExpanded] = useState(false);
// ...
const isCollapsed = status === "closed" && !closedExpanded;
```

Users may want to collapse other columns (e.g., Open when focusing on in-progress work).

## Implementation
File: `src/webview/views/KanbanBoard.tsx`

Change from single boolean to a Set tracking collapsed columns:
```tsx
const [collapsedColumns, setCollapsedColumns] = useState<Set<BeadStatus>>(
  new Set(["closed"]) // Closed collapsed by default
);

const toggleColumn = (status: BeadStatus) => {
  setCollapsedColumns(prev => {
    const next = new Set(prev);
    if (next.has(status)) next.delete(status);
    else next.add(status);
    return next;
  });
};

const isCollapsed = collapsedColumns.has(status);
```

## Design Considerations
- All column headers should be clickable (currently only Closed)
- Add visual affordance (collapse/expand icon in header)
- Persist collapsed state? (localStorage or just session)
- Collapsed column should show count prominently

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 4 columns can be collapsed/expanded
- [ ] Closed still collapsed by default
- [ ] Click any column header to toggle
- [ ] Visual indicator for collapsible headers
- [ ] Collapsed columns show item count

## Open Questions
- Persist collapse state across sessions (localStorage)?
- Add explicit collapse/expand icon or just clickable header?
- Keyboard shortcut to collapse/expand?
- Should collapsed columns have a minimum width or be truly minimal?

design:
Settings structure could be:
- `beads.colors.priority.P0`: { bg, text }
- `beads.colors.priority.P1`: { bg, text }
- `beads.colors.status.open`: { bg, text }
- `beads.colors.type.bug`: { bg, text }

Or a single object per category. Consider theme-aware defaults.
